http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/Importance-of-CME-programmes-for-docs-stressed/article14009873.ece

Innovative practices in medical education are needed and medical teachers have a great role in training the future doctors, Principal of Andhra Medical College S.V. Kumar said while inaugurating a four-day workshop on Attitudes and Communication (ATCOM) and the revised basic workshop for training in medical education technology for medical teachers at AMC here on Tuesday.Faculty members from 17 medical colleges are attending the workshop being conducted at the MCI Regional Centre for Medical Education Teachers (MET) at AMC.Former DME R. Sasi Prabha, who was the chief guest, stressed the importance of continuing medical education programmes in updating the skills of doctors both in teaching and training.